HAND, FOOT AND MOUTH DISEASE - VIET NAM (09): (DONG NAI)
********************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: 14 Jun 2012
Source: English Xinuhuanet.com [edited]
http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/health/2012-06/14/c_131652550.htm


A hand, foot and mouth disease (HFMD) epidemic has developed rapidly and unexpectedly across Viet Nam's southern Dong Nai province, warned the provincial preventive medicine center in its report released on Thursday [14 Jun 2012]. According to that report, HFMD disease spread to 169 out of 171 communes in Dong Nai province, about 1120 km south of the capital Hanoi, killing 2 and affecting 2000 local people since the beginning of this year [2012].

This is the peak time for the spread of diseases, with the number of people suffering from illnesses higher than in previous years, reported the centre. In the 1st 5 months of 2012, [nationally] 43 200 people have contracted HFMD, with 22 fatalities, across the country, according to the Vietnamese General Statistics Office.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[HFMD has spread throughout Viet Nam, involving both the capital city and most of the provinces. Dong Nai seems to be particularly badly hit. No information has been provided identifying the causative agent or agents.

The HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Viet Nam can be accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/008c. The location of the province of Dong Nai can be found in the map of the provinces of Viet Nam at: http://www.angelfire.com/co/hongnam/vnmap.html. - Mod.CP]
